m is ro-vibrational molecular\ncooling and adiabatic expansion rather than recombination or Ly alpha cooling.\nThe wind speed is considerably higher than the escape velocity at the wind base\nin most cases, hence the mass loss rate is proportional to the second power of\nthe EUV photosphere size R_euv, instead of the third, as suggested by previous\nworks...\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Oct 2017 21:19:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-11"}
